<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-24"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Unusual imperial decree published yesterday, summoning all high officials
                            to an audience at the imperial palace to-day. Purpose unknown, but
                            imperial trouble feared.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>